#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Opis"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kbookmarkmerger.1.docbook:40
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kbookmarkmerger; is a program for merging a given set of bookmarks into "
#| "the user's set of bookmarks; if the user doesn't have any bookmarks "
#| "created yet, a new bookmark list is created and the given bookmarks are "
#| "inserted into it. While doing this, &kbookmarkmerger; keeps track of "
#| "which files were merged in a previous run already, so no bookmark will "
#| "get installed to the user's bookmarks more than once. In case &kde; is "
#| "running while &kbookmarkmerger; is executed, the &kde; bookmark subsystem "
#| "will be informed of any changes to the user's bookmarks, so that all "
#| "applications accessing that information (&ie; &konqueror;) will pick the "
#| "changes up instantly."
msgid ""
"&kbookmarkmerger; is a program for merging a given set of bookmarks into the "
"user's set of bookmarks; if the user doesn't have any bookmarks created yet, "
"a new bookmark list is created and the given bookmarks are inserted into it. "
"While doing this, &kbookmarkmerger; keeps track of which files were merged "
"in a previous run already, so no bookmark will get installed to the user's "
"bookmarks more than once."
msgstr ""
"&kbookmarkmerger; je program za spajanje datih bookmarksa u korisničku listu "
"bookmarksa; ako korisnik nema kreiranih bookmarksa, nova lista bookmarksa je "
"kreirana i dati bookmarksi su dodani u nju. Dok ovo radi &kbookmarkmerger; "
"prati koji fajlovi su spojeni u prethodnom pokretanju tako da se bookmarksi "
"nece ponavljati. U slučaju da &kde; je u upotrebi kada se &kbookmarkmerger; "
"pokrene, &kde; bookmark podsistem će biti obavješten o izmjenama korisničkih "
"bookmarksa, tako da sve aplikacije koje koriste te informacije(&konqueror;) "
"će pokupiti promjene odmah."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kbookmarkmerger.1.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The traditionally used approach to achieve something like this was to use "
"carefully crafted skeleton home directories when creating a new user "
"account, to provide the user with a standard set of bookmarks. The problem "
"with this approach is that after the user account has been created, no new "
"bookmarks can be propagated."
msgstr ""
"Tradicionalni pristup da se ovako nešto dobije bio je da se koriste posebno "
"kreirani home direktoriji kada se kreira novi korisnik, da bi se korisniku "
"obezbjedio standardni set bookmarksa. Problem sa ovim pristupom je da nakon "
"što je kreiran novi korisnički račun, novi bookmarksi ne mogu biti "
"propagirani."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kbookmarkmerger.1.docbook:56
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This mechanism is useful for system administrators who want to propagate a "
"bookmark pointing to a certain document (for instance, important notes about "
"the system) to all users. Distributors might find it useful as well, for "
"instance by augmenting the software packages they supply with bookmark files "
"which &kbookmarkmerger; merges into the user's bookmark list when the "
"package is installed. That way, documentation shipped with a software "
"package is easily and visibly accessible right after the package has been "
"installed."
msgstr ""
"Ovaj mehanizam je koristan za sistemeske administratore koji žele da "
"propagiraju bookmarkse na neki dokument(naprimjer važne zabiljške o sistemu) "
"svim korisnicima. Distributori bi ga mogli naći također korisnim, na primjer "
"povećavajući softverske pakete koje distribuiraju sa bookmarks fajlovima "
"koje &kbookmarkmerger; spaja u korisničku listu bookmarksa kada su paketi "
"instalirani. Na taj način dokumentacija koja ide uz softverske pakete je "
"lahko dostupna odmah nako što je paket instaliran."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kbookmarkmerger.1.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The only parameter required by &kbookmarkmerger; is the name of a directory "
"which shall be scanned for bookmark files. All files in the given directory "
"will be considered for being merged into the user's setup. The files in the "
"given directory should be valid <acronym>XBEL</acronym> files."
msgstr ""
"Jedini parametar koji &kbookmarkmerger; zahtjeva je ime direktorija koji će "
"biti skeniran za bookmarks fajlove. Svi fajlovi u datom direktoriju će biti "
"podrazumijevani za spajanje u korisničkom podešavanju. Fajlovi u datom "
"direktoriju bi trebali biti valjani <acronym>XBEL</acronym> fajlovi."

